The New York Botanical Garden
Flora of North America

Diapensiaceae

*Galax aphylla* L.
det. D. E. Atha, 2008

United States of America. Virginia. Isle of Wight Co.
Southeast corner of the county on the Blackwater Ecological
Preserve of Old Dominion University, part of the Zuni Pine
Barrens Preserves along with Antioch Pines Natural Area
Preserve, ca 5 miles south of the town of Zuni, NW of Route
614, W of Horse Swamp, E of the Blackwater River.
36.824973°, -76.856807°. ca 4 m. (Coordinates and
elevation from hand-held gps and digital world map;
accurate to within a range of ca 10 m). Upland floodplain of
the Blackwater River; very sandy alluvium.

Herb, acaulescent; leaf blades lustrous; spikes erect; flowers
white.

Sample preserved in silica gel at NY.

Daniel Atha 6252 a                                         25 May 2008
